    <script>
        /*
        =======================================================================
        PIXEL DRAWING BOARD
        =======================================================================
        PROJECT IDEA #6: Build an interactive pixel art drawing application!
        
        STEP 1: CREATE YOUR VARIABLES
        - Create a constant for GRID_SIZE (16 for a 16x16 grid)
        - Create a variable for currentColor (start with '#000000' for black)
        - Create an empty array called grid to store all cell colors
        
        STEP 2: CREATE THE initGrid() FUNCTION
        - Get the canvas element using document.getElementById()
        - Set the grid layout with style.gridTemplateColumns
          (use template literals: `repeat(${GRID_SIZE}, 20px)`)
        - Clear any existing content with innerHTML = ''
        - Reset the grid array to empty
        - Use a for loop from 0 to (GRID_SIZE * GRID_SIZE):
          * Initialize grid[i] to white ('#ffffff')
          * Create a new div element for each cell
          * Set className to 'cell'
          * Set dataset.index to i (to track position)
          * Set background color to white
          * Add a click event listener that calls paintCell(this)
          * Append the cell to the canvas
        
        STEP 3: CREATE THE paintCell() FUNCTION
        - Takes one parameter: the cell element that was clicked
        - Get the index from cell.dataset.index (use parseInt!)
        - Change the cell's style.background to currentColor
        - Update grid[index] to store the currentColor
        
        STEP 4: SET UP COLOR BUTTON FUNCTIONALITY
        - Use document.querySelectorAll('.color-btn') to get all color buttons
        - Use forEach to add a click listener to each button:
          * Remove 'active' class from all buttons first
          * Add 'active' class to the clicked button
          * Update currentColor to the button's dataset.color value
        
        STEP 5: CREATE THE clearBoard() FUNCTION
        - Use confirm() to ask user if they're sure
        - If they confirm:
          * Call initGrid() to reset everything
          * Call showStatus('Board cleared!')
        
        STEP 6: CREATE THE saveDrawing() FUNCTION
        - Create an object with:
          * grid: your grid array
          * size: GRID_SIZE
          * timestamp: new Date().toISOString() (optional but cool!)
        - Convert the object to JSON using JSON.stringify()
        - Save to localStorage with localStorage.setItem('pixelDrawing', jsonData)
        - Call showStatus('Drawing saved successfully!')
        
        STEP 7: CREATE THE loadDrawing() FUNCTION
        - Get saved data with localStorage.getItem('pixelDrawing')
        - Check if savedData exists (if not, show "No saved drawing found!")
        - Use try-catch for error handling:
          * Parse the JSON with JSON.parse(savedData)
          * Check if the saved size matches current GRID_SIZE
          * Update your grid array with the loaded data
          * Get all cells with document.querySelectorAll('.cell')
          * Use forEach to update each cell:
            - Get the index from cell.dataset.index
            - Set cell.style.background to grid[index]
          * Call showStatus('Drawing loaded successfully!')
        - If there's an error, call showStatus('Error loading drawing!')
        
        STEP 8: CREATE THE showStatus() FUNCTION
        - Get the status element with document.getElementById('status')
        - Set its textContent to the message parameter
        - Use setTimeout() to reset the message after 2000ms (2 seconds)
          * Inside setTimeout, change textContent back to 'Click cells to draw!'
        
        STEP 9: START YOUR APPLICATION
        - Call initGrid() to set up the board when page loads
        
        TIPS:
        - Test each function as you build it using console.log()
        - Remember: array indices start at 0
        - localStorage only stores strings - that's why we use JSON!
        - The 1D array maps to 2D: index 0 is top-left, index 15 is top-right
        - Make sure to initialize the board before trying to draw!
        =======================================================================
        */
        
